402
00:23:14,715 --> 00:23:16,814
you waste no time sending reminders...

403
00:23:16,815 --> 00:23:18,554
and collecting on their debts.

404
00:23:18,555 --> 00:23:22,325
But when it comes to one company that borrowed a huge sum,

405
00:23:23,525 --> 00:23:26,164
you are so calm and merciful.

406
00:23:27,864 --> 00:23:29,333
No wonder people say...

407
00:23:29,334 --> 00:23:32,705
"it's best to steal big instead of something trivial."

408
00:23:34,104 --> 00:23:37,505
They owe us, and we say it's fine.

409
00:23:37,904 --> 00:23:39,144
So what's the problem?

410
00:23:39,444 --> 00:23:43,745
The problem is with your bank, not with me.

411
00:23:46,184 --> 00:23:47,715
What do you mean?

412
00:23:48,344 --> 00:23:51,015
Just like your Jisan Bank,

413
00:23:52,725 --> 00:23:56,025
Hanra Bank lent money to People's Entertainment.

414
00:23:57,154 --> 00:24:00,664
They just agreed to start the process of selling off...

415
00:24:01,065 --> 00:24:02,334
the bad loan.

416
00:24:05,094 --> 00:24:08,535
Sang Ah Group's chairman's son is involved in this mess,

417
00:24:10,604 --> 00:24:13,144
so the media will have a field day.

418
00:24:14,275 --> 00:24:15,545
If your shareholders...

419
00:24:16,045 --> 00:24:17,414
were to ask what was going on,

420
00:24:18,575 --> 00:24:20,844
do you have a good enough explanation ready?

421
00:24:23,315 --> 00:24:27,325
What if they ask what you were "banking on" when you lent them...

422
00:24:29,025 --> 00:24:30,624
so much money?

423
00:24:40,364 --> 00:24:43,134
Let Taeil Accounting handle it for you.

424
00:24:45,104 --> 00:24:47,344
We'll sort everything out.

425
00:25:11,164 --> 00:25:12,264
Good morning.

426
00:25:12,265 --> 00:25:13,434
- Hello. - Morning, sir.

427
00:25:16,334 --> 00:25:17,805
Here's the announcement.

428
00:25:18,604 --> 00:25:20,805
Our Taeil Accounting...

429
00:25:21,045 --> 00:25:23,745
will handle Jisan Bank's bad loan.

430
00:25:24,745 --> 00:25:26,084
Both purchase and sales.

431
00:25:29,015 --> 00:25:30,815
We'll handle it all.

432
00:25:52,075 --> 00:25:54,343
I'll explain for the sake of our new recruits.

433
00:25:54,344 --> 00:25:57,015
Our Sales Team will focus solely on selling.

434
00:25:57,215 --> 00:25:59,745
We'll set a baseline, the bare minimum we must get.

435
00:25:59,985 --> 00:26:02,884
That's the price we must get if we're to break even.

436
00:26:03,184 --> 00:26:05,653
You can't do business if you're selling something...

437
00:26:05,654 --> 00:26:07,384
without knowing the prime cost.

438
00:26:07,725 --> 00:26:09,353
The prime cost we set is the minimum sales price.

439
00:26:09,354 --> 00:26:12,724
Out of those who bid above it,

440
00:26:12,725 --> 00:26:14,624
the one who bid the most...

441
00:26:15,325 --> 00:26:16,495
wins the auction.

442
00:26:17,594 --> 00:26:19,833
What if all the bids we get...

443
00:26:19,834 --> 00:26:22,705
fall below the minimum sales price we calculated?

444
00:26:23,434 --> 00:26:25,943
If that happens, everyone in this room...

445
00:26:25,944 --> 00:26:27,745
might have to resign.

446
00:26:29,275 --> 00:26:30,744
That doesn't happen.

447
00:26:30,745 --> 00:26:32,914
If one or two bids are like that, it's one or the other.

448
00:26:33,045 --> 00:26:35,815
Their team has lost its touch, or they're not interested.

449
00:26:36,414 --> 00:26:37,913
But no one would pay the hefty fee...

450
00:26:37,914 --> 00:26:40,785
