00:33:28,594 --> 00:33:30,593
- Where's the revised contract? - Oh, right.

536
00:33:30,594 --> 00:33:32,235
It's...

537
00:33:32,394 --> 00:33:33,403
Here you go.

538
00:33:33,404 --> 00:33:34,535
I'll leave this with you.

539
00:33:34,965 --> 00:33:36,334
Wait. If we were...

540
00:33:37,404 --> 00:33:38,475
Well...

541
00:33:38,735 --> 00:33:41,545
If we were to hear anything from Sales, would it help us?

542
00:33:41,674 --> 00:33:42,774
Of course.

543
00:33:42,775 --> 00:33:45,545
We can guess how they're calculating the minimum sales price.

544
00:33:45,674 --> 00:33:48,785
If we know that, we won half the battle.

545
00:33:49,144 --> 00:33:50,455
Why? Do you know something?

546
00:33:52,515 --> 00:33:54,725
No. I just asked.

547
00:33:54,924 --> 00:33:56,025
Okay.

548
00:33:56,525 --> 00:33:57,725
Handle that for me.

549
00:34:37,835 --> 00:34:41,104
I thought you'd do anything to appeal to Sim Hyung Woo.

550
00:34:41,105 --> 00:34:43,475
- So why? - It's the power of principle.

551
00:34:43,634 --> 00:34:46,174
I won't do anything to kill others to save my skin.

552
00:34:47,404 --> 00:34:49,475
The real power is in making people act...

553
00:34:50,075 --> 00:34:51,544
without having to give orders.

554
00:34:57,585 --> 00:34:59,984
The power to make people act without giving orders.

555
00:35:10,995 --> 00:35:12,165
What's this?

556
00:35:15,404 --> 00:35:16,734
What's this doing here?

557
00:35:18,234 --> 00:35:20,504
I think Jang Ho Woo left it earlier.

558
00:35:20,975 --> 00:35:22,245
What on earth...

559
00:35:25,714 --> 00:35:27,015
In the elevator.

560
00:35:29,015 --> 00:35:31,613
He should've told me if he had left it here.

561
00:35:31,614 --> 00:35:33,484
I went to so much trouble looking for it.

562
00:35:33,785 --> 00:35:36,294
Shouldn't you be...

563
00:35:36,895 --> 00:35:38,254
thankful he returned it to you?

564
00:36:01,484 --> 00:36:02,745
Mr. Jang.

565
00:36:05,114 --> 00:36:06,424
The paper from earlier.

566
00:36:08,024 --> 00:36:09,825
Oh, that?

567
00:36:10,955 --> 00:36:12,794
I didn't look at it.

568
00:36:13,094 --> 00:36:14,124
What?

569
00:36:14,125 --> 00:36:17,535
Aren't you worried I peeked at the estimated sale price?

570
00:36:18,495 --> 00:36:19,805
It's not that.

571
00:36:20,404 --> 00:36:21,564
I'm grateful.

572
00:36:21,904 --> 00:36:23,404
It was an important document.

573
00:36:25,404 --> 00:36:27,404
I wanted to leave it in your meeting room,

574
00:36:27,904 --> 00:36:29,375
but I was too busy.

575
00:36:29,745 --> 00:36:30,843
It's okay.

576
00:36:30,844 --> 00:36:34,384
I was waiting for you to thank you.

577
00:36:34,645 --> 00:36:36,185
Giving it to me was enough.

578
00:36:39,384 --> 00:36:40,754
I'll treat you one day.

579
00:36:41,024 --> 00:36:42,654
I know a good gukbap place.

580
00:36:43,955 --> 00:36:45,355
Okay.

581
00:36:46,694 --> 00:36:47,924
See you tomorrow.

582
00:36:55,234 --> 00:36:57,234
(Jisan Bank)

583
00:36:58,174 --> 00:37:00,003
What do you mean by making a new package...

584
00:37:00,004 --> 00:37:01,904
to sell bad loans with People's Entertainment's?

585
00:37:02,404 --> 00:37:04,813
Problematic bad loans you're keeping hidden,

586
00:37:04,814 --> 00:37:08,415
hoping no one will find out and penalize you until you resign.

587
00:37:09,214 --> 00:37:10,384
You have a few.

588
00:37:10,814 --> 00:37:12,415
Don't be silly.

589
00:37:12,924 --> 00:37:14,455
There's no such thing.

590
00:37:14,725 --> 00:37:16,955
When you sell People's bad loans,

591
00:37:17,094 --> 00:37:18,325
discard those too.

592
00:37:21,794 --> 00:37:23,094
Think about it.

593
00:37:23,435 --> 00:37:24,794
Would that even be possible?

594
00:37:25,535 --> 00:37:27,304
Taeil Accounting insisted...

595
00:37:27,305 --> 00:37:29,904
we gave them the best products...

596
00:37:30,035 --> 00:37:31,805
because we needed this deal to work out.

597
00:37:32,504 --> 00:37:34,645
This won't go to Taeil Accounting.

598
00:37:35,044 --> 00:37:36,645
I'll handle it for you.

599
00:37:37,274 --> 00:37:38,544
At a great price.

600
00:37:42,245 --> 00:37:45,014
Whatever's in the package, the buyer is set and ready.

601
00:37:45,015 --> 00:37:47,254
Don't worry about the deal falling through.

602
00:37:49,355 --> 00:37:50,895
What's your condition?

603
00:37:51,855 --> 00:37:53,825
Do business with me only from now on.

604
00:37:54,495 --> 00:37:56,064
That means to Jisan Bank,

605
00:37:56,794 --> 00:37:58,335
I am Taeil Accounting.

606
00:38:04,134 --> 00:38:07,245
You can't switch the product without a hint to us.

607
00:38:07,875 --> 00:38:09,544
Who would buy trash like this?

608
00:38:10,145 --> 00:38:11,544
What do you expect me to do now?

609
00:38:17,314 --> 00:38:19,285
Are you out of your mind?

610
00:38:19,515 --> 00:38:23,825
I'm heartbroken that Kang Hyun ruined the M and A.

611
00:38:23,995 --> 00:38:25,154
How dare you...

612
00:38:25,424 --> 00:38:27,964
ruin the bad loan deal too?

613
00:38:28,094 --> 00:38:29,864
It's not ruined, so don't worry.

614
00:38:30,535 --> 00:38:33,264
Sang Ah Group's Chairman Lee will have no choice but to buy.

615
00:38:33,265 --> 00:38:36,734
Lee Chan Ju is not mad enough to buy trash.

616
00:38:36,805 --> 00:38:39,134
He might not want it, of course,

617
00:38:39,205 --> 00:38:41,604
but he'll like it even less if anyone else were to buy it.

618
00:38:41,605 --> 00:38:43,844
No, wait.

619
00:38:43,975 --> 00:38:45,814
He'd be more afraid.

620
00:38:45,944 --> 00:38:49,915
Are you saying someone is threatening him with trash?

621
00:38:50,154 --> 00:38:51,313
The right to view accounts.

622
00:38:51,314 --> 00:38:53,225
What about the right to view...

623
00:38:59,594 --> 00:39:01,064
The right to view the books?

624
00:39:01,665 --> 00:39:04,164
Whoever buys the bad loans of People's Entertainment...

625
00:39:04,165 --> 00:39:07,733
gains the right to view their financial statements...

626
00:39:07,734 --> 00:39:10,504
as well as any account, and they can do so at any time.

627
00:39:12,035 --> 00:39:17,444
It's a Pandora's Box for Sang Ah Group's heir, Bo Sung.

628
00:39:18,575 --> 00:39:20,884
Who do you think would want that the most?

629
00:39:23,254 --> 00:39:24,254
Keep going.

630
00:39:26,114 --> 00:39:28,555
Lee Chan Ju's younger brother, Lee Sung Ju.

631
00:39:30,094 --> 00:39:32,023
Despite being better than his older brother,

632
00:39:32,024 --> 00:39:33,825
he was kicked out of Sang Ah Group.

633
00:39:35,194 --> 00:39:36,364
The unfortunate...

634
00:39:37,765 --> 00:39:38,835
prince.

635
00:39:39,265 --> 00:39:40,733
If it hadn't been for his father,

636
00:39:40,734 --> 00:39:43,274
he'd have become chairman long ago.

637
00:39:43,705 --> 00:39:45,904
It's a shame on his part.

638
00:39:53,085 --> 00:39:54,844
Are you saying...

639
00:39:56,355 --> 00:39:59,555
you'll participate in this deal as Lee Sung Ju's proxy?

640
00:40:01,085 --> 00:40:03,555
Wouldn't there be a reason he amassed a fortune...

641
00:40:03,855 --> 00:40:06,464
at the expense of being called a loan shark?

642
00:40:07,694 --> 00:40:08,964
Perhaps...

643
00:40:09,964 --> 00:40:12,464
he wants to regain what he has lost.

644
00:40:15,504 --> 00:40:18,975
I think the actual product of this bad loan deal...

645
00:40:19,705 --> 00:40:22,274
is the right to view People's account books.

646
00:40:25,774 --> 00:40:27,114
Don't you agree?

647
00:40:38,825 --> 00:40:40,165
The right to view accounts?

648
00:40:40,325 --> 00:40:41,894
If that had been such a great thing,

649
00:40:41,895 --> 00:40:43,994
you should've told me.

650
00:40:43,995 --> 00:40:46,233
The right to view accounts isn't a great thing.

651
00:40:46,234 --> 00:40:48,503
It's an ordinary right given to anyone...

652
00:40:48,504 --> 00:40:50,233
who owns a certain percentage of a company.

653
00:40:50,234 --> 00:40:53,304
Are you saying Sung Ju can turn this place...

654
00:40:53,305 --> 00:40:55,274
into a mess over something that ordinary?

655
00:40:56,344 --> 00:40:57,744
Other than embezzlement or negligence,

656
00:40:57,745 --> 00:40:59,914
was your son up to...

657
00:40:59,915 --> 00:41:01,014
anything else?

658
00:41:01,015 --> 00:41:03,984
I'm losing my mind because I don't know.

659
00:41:04,355 --> 00:41:06,484
He caused so much trouble all over the place.

660
00:41:10,455 --> 00:41:12,653
Sung Ju is annoyingly tenacious.

661
00:41:12,654 --> 00:41:15,694
You know how hard it was when we kicked him out.

662
00:41:15,794 --> 00:41:18,464
And to think he might get his hands on the accounts?

663
00:41:19,165 --> 00:41:20,804
It'll be the death of me,

664
00:41:20,805 --> 00:41:22,404
Bo Sung, and everyone.

665
00:41:22,535 --> 00:41:23,805
No, it can't happen.

666
00:41:23,875 --> 00:41:25,674
It must be stopped at all costs.

667
00:41:31,714 --> 00:41:32,814
I'll buy it.

668
00:41:33,044 --> 00:41:35,414
Whether it's for 10 million or 100 million dollars, I'll buy it.

669
00:41:35,415 --> 00:41:38,714
Bring it right in front of me!

670
00:42:08,785 --> 00:42:10,555
Did you say to send Jang Ho Woo to your team?

671
00:42:10,884 --> 00:42:12,614
You heard me.

672
00:42:13,384 --> 00:42:15,085
Tell him to be on time for the meeting tomorrow.

673
00:42:16,995 --> 00:42:18,094
Is that all?

674
00:42:18,594 --> 00:42:20,394
I know he only graduated high school,

675
00:42:20,395 --> 00:42:22,225
but you still need to give me a reason.

676
00:42:22,725 --> 00:42:24,894
You're not going to train him nor make use of him.

677
00:42:24,895 --> 00:42:26,394
So why does it matter to you if I take him?

678
00:42:26,395 --> 00:42:27,805
He's just a graduate accountant.

679
00:42:30,535 --> 00:42:32,805
I decide how we'll use him.

680
00:42:33,105 --> 00:42:34,444
I'm not going to say it twice.

681
00:42:34,904 --> 00:42:36,105
Send him to me.

682
00:42:36,544 --> 00:42:38,174
Don't make anyone end up like you again.

683
00:42:49,254 --> 00:42:51,254
Why do you get to choose where I stay?

684
00:42:51,495 --> 00:42:54,193
Do I have to move and leave your team...

685
00:42:54,194 --> 00:42:56,194
upon your request?

686
00:42:56,395 --> 00:42:59,035
Do you not know what it means to be a salaryman?

687
00:42:59,864 --> 00:43:01,205
If you're trying to find out...

688
00:43:01,435 --> 00:43:05,003
Director Sim Hyung Woo's bid price,

689
00:43:05,004 --> 00:43:06,174
you should give up now.

690
00:43:07,205 --> 00:43:08,974
As an accountant,

691
00:43:08,975 --> 00:43:11,213
I'd never let that happen.

692
00:43:11,214 --> 00:43:12,645
Or is it because you know nothing?

693
00:43:15,085 --> 00:43:16,085
I'm leaving.

694
00:43:19,415 --> 00:43:21,124
I have an appointment with Gampyeong Corporation.

695
00:43:21,125 --> 00:43:22,125
I don't have time to fool around with you.

696
00:43:22,126 --> 00:43:24,554
I was there for a reason.

697
00:43:24,555 --> 00:43:25,995
There's something I must do.

698
00:43:33,404 --> 00:43:35,205
Why are you doing this to me?

699
00:43:35,805 --> 00:43:38,004
Why do you keep interrupting my plan?

700
00:43:39,705 --> 00:43:41,875
If you stay there, you'll get hurt.

701
00:43:43,344 --> 00:43:44,914
And you have no power...

702
00:43:44,915 --> 00:43:46,714
or anyone who can help you get back on your feet.

703
00:43:47,745 --> 00:43:50,714
Once you fall down, your whole plan will go to waste.

704
00:43:59,225 --> 00:44:00,265
What?

705
00:44:03,364 --> 00:44:04,535
What did he say?

706
00:44:05,064 --> 00:44:09,464
He said I had no power or anyone who could help me get back on my feet.

707
00:44:09,705 --> 00:44:10,804
How could he?

708
00:44:10,805 --> 00:44:14,074
Tell that lunatic that I'll give him a sound beating tomorrow.

709
00:44:14,075 --> 00:44:15,443
He dares to mess with Ho Woo?

710
00:44:15,444 --> 00:44:16,974
I'll tell him to come here, and when he comes,

711
00:44:16,975 --> 00:44:19,244
I'll throw an uppercut on the count of two...

712
00:44:19,245 --> 00:44:20,285
Hey.

713
00:44:20,844 --> 00:44:22,415
- Stay quiet. - Sorry.

714
00:44:24,415 --> 00:44:25,514
I'll do it.

715
00:44:25,515 --> 00:44:28,125
I'll quit my job if I have to tomorrow.

716
00:44:28,924 --> 00:44:31,855
I'll smash that jerk's head.

717
00:44:32,024 --> 00:44:34,165
I'm serious.

718
00:44:39,634 --> 00:44:41,805
"If you stay there, you'll get hurt."

719
00:44:42,734 --> 00:44:44,904
It felt weird when he said that.

720
00:44:45,035 --> 00:44:47,503
So? Did you find that romantic?

721
00:44:47,504 --> 00:44:48,544
Enough.

722
00:44:51,475 --> 00:44:52,475
Well,

723
00:44:52,944 --> 00:44:56,145
I could feel his sincerity.

724
00:44:57,455 --> 00:45:00,124
You shouldn't feel a man's sincerity that easily.

725
00:45:00,125 --> 00:45:01,725
Seriously, you guys!

726
00:45:02,654 --> 00:45:05,554
How come you're never helpful to me ever?

727
00:45:05,555 --> 00:45:08,225
Didn't I say this was the night of the plan?

728
00:45:10,165 --> 00:45:12,233
Do you have the confidentiality agreement ready?

729
00:45:12,234 --> 00:45:13,435
Yes, here it is.

730
00:45:17,435 --> 00:45:18,633
What about the financing plan report?

731
00:45:18,634 --> 00:45:20,805
It'll be ready as soon as we receive the loan confirmation.

732
00:45:21,575 --> 00:45:23,745
Even at the lowest price,

733
00:45:24,015 --> 00:45:26,043
the final price would be over 50.

734
00:45:26,044 --> 00:45:27,214
The bid price should be...

735
00:45:31,285 --> 00:45:33,523
(Bidding Price, 58 million dollars)

736
00:45:33,524 --> 00:45:36,325
(Bidding Price, 60.1 million dollars)

737
00:45:36,725 --> 00:45:38,754
Have you confirmed the evaluation report on Banbo Assets?

738
00:45:39,424 --> 00:45:40,564
Yes, I've confirmed it.

739
00:45:46,705 --> 00:45:47,705
(Investor's Perspective)

740
00:45:48,035 --> 00:45:49,904
What do you think? I think it looks good.

741
00:45:52,875 --> 00:45:54,044
Sure. Let's go with it.

742
00:45:56,714 --> 00:45:58,774
- Jang Ho Woo. - Yes?

743
00:46:10,924 --> 00:46:12,394
Did you leave the bidding price blank?

744
00:46:12,395 --> 00:46:14,423
Yes, you said you'd write it when we got there.

745
00:46:14,424 --> 00:46:16,764
Don't forget all kinds of things happen on the day of bidding.

746
00:46:16,765 --> 00:46:17,935
Pull yourself together.

747
00:46:18,634 --> 00:46:19,634
Yes.

748
00:46:31,814 --> 00:46:33,174
I said to pull yourself together.

749
00:46:43,924 --> 00:46:44,995
Get ready.

750
00:47:10,785 --> 00:47:11,785
Darn it.

751
00:47:16,384 --> 00:47:17,855
It looks like someone's here to greet us.

752
00:47:22,765 --> 00:47:23,765
How much time do we have left?

753
00:47:24,864 --> 00:47:25,864
About 40 minutes.

754
00:48:25,455 --> 00:48:26,495
Watch out.

755
00:48:51,884 --> 00:48:53,254
Are you okay?

756
00:48:53,384 --> 00:48:55,055
I'm okay.

757
00:48:56,085 --> 00:48:57,225
So is the proposal.

758
00:49:01,825 --> 00:49:04,134
I guess there was one more car following us.

759
00:49:05,134 --> 00:49:07,605
It's the same model.

760
00:49:18,075 --> 00:49:19,714
Come out. Now!

761
00:49:22,015 --> 00:49:23,614
Who sent you? Answer me.

762
00:49:24,355 --> 00:49:25,814
I asked you a question!

763
00:49:26,415 --> 00:49:27,484
Was it Director Han?

764
00:49:27,955 --> 00:49:29,184
Answer me.

765
00:49:29,185 --> 00:49:30,954
- Answer me now... - Calm down.

766
00:49:30,955 --> 00:49:33,125
- Mr. Han. - Unhand me!

767
00:49:33,225 --> 00:49:34,395
Calm down, will you?

768
00:49:35,725 --> 00:49:37,165
Who sent you?

769
00:49:39,294 --> 00:49:41,204
He hit me first.

770
00:49:41,205 --> 00:49:42,435
Stay right there.

771
00:49:45,475 --> 00:49:47,403
Jang Ho Woo, we have no time to waste here.

772
00:49:47,404 --> 00:49:49,705
Head to Jisan Bank with the proposal first.

773
00:49:49,774 --> 00:49:51,575
You know we have to submit it on time.

774
00:49:51,745 --> 00:49:52,944
- Yes. - Hurry up.

775
00:50:09,464 --> 00:50:10,464
What's wrong?

776
00:50:15,134 --> 00:50:16,134
What is it?

777
00:50:21,444 --> 00:50:22,805
The proposal is gone.

778
00:50:33,825 --> 00:50:36,584
(J Bank NPL Bidding Proposal Submission)

779
00:50:36,585 --> 00:50:37,625
What?

780
00:50:38,395 --> 00:50:39,995
The price isn't written?

781
00:50:42,794 --> 00:50:44,535
Okay. Well done.

782
00:50:45,765 --> 00:50:46,794
All right.

783
00:50:47,564 --> 00:50:48,964
Let's hand it in now.

784
00:50:50,734 --> 00:50:51,734
What about them?

785
00:50:51,835 --> 00:50:53,305
I took care of it.

786
00:50:53,605 --> 00:50:55,075
Come on. Let's hand it in.

787
00:50:55,544 --> 00:50:57,515
The bidding will end soon.

788
00:51:00,785 --> 00:51:01,785
Come on.

789
00:51:02,714 --> 00:51:03,884
Wait.

790
00:51:12,555 --> 00:51:16,194
Here is SA Investment's bidding proposal.

791
00:51:18,364 --> 00:51:20,093
(SA Investment)

792
00:51:20,094 --> 00:51:21,105
(Jang Ho Woo of Taeil Accounting)

793
00:51:26,435 --> 00:51:27,774
That is impossible.

794
00:51:33,475 --> 00:51:36,214
(The proposal)

795
00:51:39,314 --> 00:51:40,855
(Jang Ho Woo)

796
00:51:57,435 --> 00:52:01,145
Police don't have the authority to block the road like this!

797
00:52:01,245 --> 00:52:03,043
We've got a report.

798
00:52:03,044 --> 00:52:04,244
If you don't cooperate,

799
00:52:04,245 --> 00:52:07,415
you'll be punished according to Article Five of the Traffic Law.

800
00:52:14,125 --> 00:52:15,825
The report on the fallen object is settled.

801
00:52:16,225 --> 00:52:17,254
"A fallen object?"

802
00:52:17,325 --> 00:52:18,955
What fallen object in this jurisdiction?

803
00:52:19,154 --> 00:52:20,224
Who are you?

804
00:52:20,225 --> 00:52:22,964
I was told jurisdiction does not matter when it comes to prevention.

805
00:52:25,835 --> 00:52:27,234
Hello.

806
00:52:30,504 --> 00:52:32,835
There is no one named Jang Ho Woo here.

807
00:52:33,274 --> 00:52:34,375
He'll be here soon.

808
00:52:34,444 --> 00:52:35,575
I'm here!

809
00:52:37,674 --> 00:52:38,774
I am...

810
00:52:39,674 --> 00:52:40,984
Jang Ho Woo.

811
00:52:41,785 --> 00:52:42,944
Here you are.

812
00:52:59,535 --> 00:53:00,664
Can you...

813
00:53:00,665 --> 00:53:02,605
give us five minutes to discuss something?

814
00:53:10,205 --> 00:53:13,074
Even this current price is ten million dollars higher...

815
00:53:13,075 --> 00:53:15,285
than the 60.1 million dollars I first suggested.

816
00:53:15,384 --> 00:53:17,043
If you raise the price,

817
00:53:17,044 --> 00:53:19,084
you're paying way more...

818
00:53:19,085 --> 00:53:21,125
than what you paid for People's Entertainment.

819
00:53:21,254 --> 00:53:22,383
I know that.

820
00:53:22,384 --> 00:53:23,824
I know that too.

821
00:53:23,825 --> 00:53:27,564
But when I think about Lee Sung Ju taking the log...

822
00:53:28,125 --> 00:53:29,463
What if things go south with Bo Sung?

823
00:53:29,464 --> 00:53:31,035
What's the point of all this money?

824
00:53:32,794 --> 00:53:35,265
Ninety million dollars. Write 90 million to be safe.

825
00:53:35,335 --> 00:53:36,464
Chairman Lee.

826
00:53:36,605 --> 00:53:38,233
The current price is more than enough.

827
00:53:38,234 --> 00:53:40,173
You already have a high chance of winning the bid.

828
00:53:40,174 --> 00:53:41,903
I'm not looking for a high chance.

829
00:53:41,904 --> 00:53:43,805
I need confidence.

830
00:53:44,674 --> 00:53:45,774
Write it.

831
00:53:49,915 --> 00:53:51,085
Here.

832
00:53:53,714 --> 00:53:54,725
(Bidding Proposal)

833
00:53:57,594 --> 00:53:59,694
(Bidding Price, 90.1 million dollars)

834
00:54:02,495 --> 00:54:03,794
(Bidding Price, 90.1 million dollars)

835
00:54:04,964 --> 00:54:06,064
Darn it.

836
00:54:07,634 --> 00:54:10,435
Do you think he'd listen to you?

837
00:54:12,105 --> 00:54:14,245
If he wants to rave, let him.

838
00:54:16,904 --> 00:54:18,844
The more Chairman Lee pays,

839
00:54:19,375 --> 00:54:21,484
the more we'll get paid.

840
00:54:22,844 --> 00:54:24,814
We have nothing to lose.

841
00:54:26,915 --> 00:54:28,154
Don't you think?

842
00:54:42,535 --> 00:54:44,003
We'll now announce the minimum sales price...

843
00:54:44,004 --> 00:54:46,605
and the bidding prices.

844
00:54:49,305 --> 00:54:50,814
The minimum sales price...

845
00:54:51,015 --> 00:54:52,874
is 54.6 million dollars.

846
00:54:52,875 --> 00:54:55,584
- What happened? - Bids above 54.6 million...

847
00:54:55,585 --> 00:54:56,813
- will win the bidding. - You said all kinds of things...

848
00:54:56,814 --> 00:54:57,915
happened on the day of the bidding.

849
00:54:58,314 --> 00:54:59,415
That's what.

850
00:55:02,685 --> 00:55:04,125
First Investment Trusts...

851
00:55:04,455 --> 00:55:06,794
bids 54.9 million dollars.

852
00:55:09,194 --> 00:55:12,364
Sang Ah Group Holdings bids 90.1 million dollars.

853
00:55:17,165 --> 00:55:19,004
(Jisan Bank Non-performing Loan Sales Auction)

854
00:55:19,975 --> 00:55:21,104
Lastly,

855
00:55:21,105 --> 00:55:23,004
SA Investment.

856
00:55:25,674 --> 00:55:27,444
Thirty-three million dollars.

857
00:55:38,794 --> 00:55:41,665
I hereby announce People's Entertainment's...

858
00:55:41,694 --> 00:55:44,935
eight non-performing loans are auctioned to Sang Ah Group Holdings.

859
00:55:53,435 --> 00:55:55,774
(Jisan Bank Non-performing Loan Sales Auction)

860
00:56:02,844 --> 00:56:04,914
This is Han Seung Jo of Taeil Accounting.

861
00:56:04,915 --> 00:56:06,055
Chairman Lee Sung Ju.

862
00:56:06,884 --> 00:56:08,024
Someone just told me...

863
00:56:08,225 --> 00:56:11,254
that real power was making others move on their own...

864
00:56:11,355 --> 00:56:14,424
even without using their power.

865
00:56:14,725 --> 00:56:16,793
I think the only person who can make Chairman Lee Chan Ju move...

866
00:56:16,794 --> 00:56:18,835
just with imagination and fear is...

867
00:56:20,265 --> 00:56:22,064
you, Chairman Lee Sung Ju.

868
00:56:24,435 --> 00:56:26,435
So? You want to borrow my name?

869
00:56:27,475 --> 00:56:28,575
Yes.

870
00:56:29,105 --> 00:56:31,415
Lee Chan Ju of SA Investment.

871
00:56:32,044 --> 00:56:33,314
I need that name.

872
00:56:38,555 --> 00:56:39,714
Sounds good to me.

873
00:56:40,355 --> 00:56:42,855
Just put it back to where it was after using it.

874
00:56:43,484 --> 00:56:46,694
Everything goes back to where they were before.

875
00:56:47,254 --> 00:56:48,423
Thank you.

876
00:56:48,424 --> 00:56:51,134
I'm not interested in the entertainment business at all,

877
00:56:51,794 --> 00:56:53,464
but this is intriguing.

878
00:56:53,995 --> 00:56:55,165
Especially...

879
00:56:55,734 --> 00:56:58,535
the owner's risk of spending company funds...

880
00:57:00,004 --> 00:57:01,774
for his personal reasons.

881
00:57:06,915 --> 00:57:08,145
I hope you win.

882
00:57:08,884 --> 00:57:12,185
I'll win by losing.

883
00:57:19,294 --> 00:57:21,725
When he said 90.1 million dollars, I almost screamed.

884
00:57:32,875 --> 00:57:34,605
Congratulations on winning the bid.

885
00:57:36,745 --> 00:57:39,515
You would've still won with 60 million dollars.

886
00:57:40,015 --> 00:57:41,684
It must be because you're rich.

887
00:57:41,685 --> 00:57:42,915
Your bid was extreme.

888
00:57:43,044 --> 00:57:44,154
I'm impressed.

889
00:58:09,205 --> 00:58:11,515
Take advantage of your opponent's weakness.

890
00:58:14,515 --> 00:58:15,984
Well done.

891
00:58:16,915 --> 00:58:18,185
It was a good choice.

892
00:58:20,314 --> 00:58:23,024
My opponent will soon be you, Father.

893
00:58:25,395 --> 00:58:27,055
Oh, no.

894
00:58:28,524 --> 00:58:29,725
No way.

895
00:58:31,765 --> 00:58:33,694
No matter what you say today,

896
00:58:34,935 --> 00:58:38,274
it will not ruin my day.

897
00:58:39,875 --> 00:58:41,273
Both as your father...

898
00:58:41,274 --> 00:58:44,245
and as the vice president of Taeil Accounting,

899
00:58:46,944 --> 00:58:48,745
I'm satisfied.

900
00:58:54,654 --> 00:58:55,754
Right?

901
00:59:06,765 --> 00:59:08,064
Mr. Han.

902
00:59:11,634 --> 00:59:14,474
Is there an accountant from Taeil Accounting here?

903
00:59:14,475 --> 00:59:15,903
Yes, right here.

904
00:59:15,904 --> 00:59:19,774
You get your job done just perfectly.

905
00:59:20,915 --> 00:59:23,114
That's what he's known for.

906
00:59:23,515 --> 00:59:26,015
He points out...

907
00:59:26,185 --> 00:59:27,725
to the bottom line.

908
00:59:28,125 --> 00:59:29,454
That's why everyone likes him.

909
00:59:29,455 --> 00:59:33,325
I've already seen that in the case of Haebit Construction.

910
00:59:33,694 --> 00:59:34,764
To be honest,

911
00:59:34,765 --> 00:59:37,764
there were a lot of discussions...

912
00:59:37,765 --> 00:59:39,765
on whether we should make Haebit Construction close or not.

913
00:59:39,995 --> 00:59:43,834
Mr. Han Seung Jo, standing right here, concluded...

914
00:59:43,835 --> 00:59:45,504
that they should be closed.

915
00:59:45,805 --> 00:59:48,844
So we pushed to liquidation right away.

916
00:59:52,544 --> 00:59:53,544
Watch...

917
00:59:53,545 --> 00:59:55,544
what this piece of paper written by an accounting firm...

918
00:59:56,245 --> 00:59:57,984
can do from here on.

919
01:00:17,504 --> 01:00:19,174
- I'll get going. - Yes.

920
01:00:23,404 --> 01:00:25,075
Shall we get going?

921
01:00:30,984 --> 01:00:32,314
Why did you do that?

922
01:00:35,785 --> 01:00:36,884
What?

923
01:00:43,464 --> 01:00:44,765
About Haebit Construction.

924
01:00:52,975 --> 01:00:55,145
Why did you make the decision...

925
01:00:55,404 --> 01:00:57,274
to liquidate the company?

926
01:01:00,114 --> 01:01:02,844
One's life isn't a joke.

927
01:01:05,055 --> 01:01:06,285
How could you?

928
01:01:44,955 --> 01:01:46,924
(Numbers)

929
01:01:47,424 --> 01:01:49,994
The report on Haebit Construction liquidation decision.

930
01:01:49,995 --> 01:01:51,164
Where is it now?

931
01:01:51,165 --> 01:01:53,863
Han Seung Jo will be in charge of this project,

932
01:01:53,864 --> 01:01:55,563
and I should be a backup manager.

933
01:01:55,564 --> 01:01:56,764
Where's the rest?

934
01:01:56,765 --> 01:01:59,273
Do you want to see it? Then work on my team.

935
01:01:59,274 --> 01:02:00,903
It's not about trusting each other.

936
01:02:00,904 --> 01:02:03,443
This is a strategic alliance to achieve our own goals.

937
01:02:03,444 --> 01:02:05,213
Because selling it will bring more money...

938
01:02:05,214 --> 01:02:06,244
than keeping it alive.

939
01:02:06,245 --> 01:02:07,543
You think it's fun to play with me?

940
01:02:07,544 --> 01:02:10,745
Did you get something in return for liquidation?

941
01:02:10,785 --> 01:02:13,254
How much more do I have to sell to make you happy?

942
01:02:13,355 --> 01:02:14,684
Your best decision is...

943
01:02:14,685 --> 01:02:17,355
creating the worst decision for others.

944
01:02:17,455 --> 01:02:19,725
I won't let you live in peace...

945
01:02:19,995 --> 01:02:22,794
as if nothing happened until now.